In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. reflects on Father's Day and the importance of fathers in shaping the next generation. He emphasizes the sacrifices, guidance, and unconditional love that fathers provide, and how they teach values and foster healthy perspectives on masculinity. President Biden shares personal memories of his own father and the lessons he learned from him. He also discusses his commitment to building the economy, protecting social security and Medicare, and delivering affordable child care and paid family leave. He acknowledges the difficulty that Father's Day can bring for those who have lost their fathers or children, but emphasizes that the love between fathers and their loved ones is a gift that never goes away. The article concludes with President Biden proclaiming June 18, 2023, as Father's Day and calling for the display of the United States flag on all government buildings to honor fathers.